(File) (Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A man was found shot dead on the side of a road in Maraisburg, Johannesburg, on Tuesday, paramedics said.He was killed in Millward Street, Netcare 911 spokesperson Santi Steinmann said."The man died due to the extensive injury sustained during the shooting."He was in his 20s. "It is alleged that the man was on his way to work when two suspects shot him once in the upper body," police spokesperson Augustinah Selepe said.He died on the scene. The killers fled in a blue BMW.Nothing was taken from the victim and the motive for the murder was unknown. The man was shot on Millward Street, about 100m from his work. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.